metadata.title: Piper Aerostar
aws::graph::propositions: Piper Aerostar Aircraft Models and Specifications
Piper Aerostar had 206 aircraft built
Piper Aerostar 600E was a designation used for aircraft sold in Europe
Piper Aerostar 601 was later designated as PA-60-601
Piper Aerostar 601 still holds the land closed speed record for a production piston twin
Piper Aerostar 601 was Model 600 with 290 hp turbocharged Lycoming TIO-540 engines
Piper Aerostar 601 had 117 aircraft built
Piper Aerostar 601B was Model 601 with increased wingspan
Piper Aerostar 601B had improved turbo system
Piper Aerostar 601B had 44 aircraft built
Piper Aerostar 601P was later designated as PA-60-601P
Piper Aerostar 601P was a pressurized version of 601
Piper Aerostar 601P had increased gross weight
Piper Aerostar 601P had increased wingspan
Piper Aerostar 601P had improved turbo system from 601B
Piper Aerostar 601P had 492 aircraft built
Piper Aerostar 602P Sequoya was later designated as PA-60-602P
Piper Aerostar 602P Sequoya was a Piper-developed version of 601P
Piper Aerostar 602P Sequoya had 290 hp Lycoming TIO-540-AA1A5 engines
Piper Aerostar 602P Sequoya had 124 aircraft built
Piper Aerostar 620 was the prototype pressurized Aerostar
Piper Aerostar 620 had 310 hp (230 kW) TIO-540 engines
